            “No [insert protected class] need apply.” Such overt discrimination
            is relatively rare today, but other practices — such as imposing
            restrictions on families with children — still occur.
          </p>
          <p>
            An example of unintentional discrimination may be when a landlord or
            property manager applies a “one strike” tenant screening rule for
